author: PETER SUROWSKI
title: PALM SPRINGS: Woman fatally struck by train ID'd
text:
By PETER SUROWSKI / STAFF 16, 2015 Updated: 12:21 p.m. A woman who died when a train struck her near Palm Springs was identified Friday, Oct. 16.
Kiikoshawnettï¿½ Womack, a 35-year-old Palm Desert woman, was killed about 500 feet west of the Palm Springs Amtrack station, Riverside County coroners announced in a news release.
The woman was struck about 11:30 a.m. Thursday by a Union Pacific train, said Francisco Castillo, spokesman for the railroad.
The incident is being investigated as a suicide because Womack had taken an Uber car to the station and confided in the driver that she was contemplating killing herself, Castillo said.
The driver contacted the police department immediately after dropping her off, but she was dead by the time officers arrived, Castillo said.
